President Obama has nominated Antony Blinken to be the next Deputy Secretary of State. The President has known and worked closely with Blinken for the past decade, and has great respect for his knowledge, judgment, and inclusive approach to foreign policy. Blinken is described as a person of integrity with a strong work ethic and love for his country. If confirmed by the Senate, Blinken is expected to continue to do a great job representing the United States overseas on behalf of the Obama Administration.